==Development==
''Kampfgruppe'' was designed by [[Gary Grigsby]] and released in 1985, the same year he launched ''[[U.S.A.A.F. - United States Army Air Force]]'' and ''[[Mech Brigade]]''.<ref name=guru>{{cite magazine | author=Emrich, Alan | title=The Pioneering Spirit of a Wargame Guru | date=September 1995 | issue=134 | magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] | pages=201, 202, 204 }}</ref> He chose to incorporate [[Line of sight (video games)|line of sight]] in ''Kampfgruppe'', a first for a [[Strategic Simulations]] title.<ref name=retrogamerfeature /> Its design has been compared to that of ''[[PanzerBlitz]]'';<ref name=computerplay /><ref name=currentnotes>{{cite journal | author=Brooks, M. Evan | title=Battle Bytes; ''Kampfgruppe'' | volume=5 | number=5 | journal=Current Notes | date=June 1985 | pages=12, 13 }}</ref> J. L. Miller of ''Computer Play'' dubbed it "the computer version of ''PanzerBlitz''".<ref name=computerplay />

